SIMPLE: zymotic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zymotic
<hw>Zy*mot"ic</hw> <pr>(z⟦isl⟧*m⟦ocr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>zymwtiko`s</grk> causing to ferment, fr.
<grk>zymoy^n</grk> to ferment, <grk>zy`mh</grk> ferment, leaven.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of, pertaining to, or caused by,
fermentation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Designating, or pertaining to, a
certain class of diseases. See <cref>Zymotic disease</cref>,
below.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Zymotic disease</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd> any
epidemic, endemic, contagious, or sporadic affection which is produced
by some morbific principle or organism acting on the system like a
ferment.</cd></cs> <note>Now (2004) referred to as an
<altname>infectious disease</altname>. -- PJC</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zythem</ent>⟦br⟧
